http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Sarathi-Seva%E2%80%99-now-available-at-Udupi-station/article13975936.ece

Konkan Railway Corporation Ltd (KRCL) has extended its ‘Sarathi Seva’ Service for the physically challenged passengers to the Udupi Railway Station.A press release issued by KRCL here on Friday said that in this service, a wheel-chair along with an assistant was provided for free to physically challenged passengers to help the latter to get in and out of the coach at nominated stations.The scheme available at Chiplun, Ratnagiri, Karmali and Madgaon had been extended to Udupi railway station.Passengers are required to simply send an SMS with their names and journey particulars to 9664044456. The service is then arranged by KRCL.So far about 175 physically challenged passengers have availed of this service, the release added.A separate press release issued by the KRCL here said that a new ATM machine of Saraswat Bank had installed at Udupi Railway Station on Friday. Passengers could make use of this facility, the release added.